{
  "doc_id": "51439",
  "text": "Accessibility was evaluated in the same way as in Ref. [CITATION_1] . Any 7-mer in the 39UTR sequence (including seed matches) was catalogued as accessible if it contained at least one 4-mer unpaired with a probability P free $P cutoff , where P cutoff had an optimized value of 0.2. Calculation of P free values for all 4-mers in all the human 39UTR sequences was performed with the program RNAplfold [CITATION_2] using a window W = 80 and a maximum pairing distance L = 40 as recommended in Ref. [CITATION_3] .",
